===Etymology===
{{PIE root|en|bʰuH|h₁es|h₂wes}}
From {{inh|en|enm|been||to be}}. The various forms have three separate origins, which were mixed together at various times in the history of English.
* The forms beginning with ''b-'' come from {{inh|en|ang|bēon||to be, become}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*beuną||to be, exist, come to be, become}}, from {{inh|en|ine-pro|*bʰúHt||to grow, become, come into being, appear}}, from the root {{m|ine-pro|*bʰuH-}}.
* The forms beginning with ''w-'' come from the aforementioned {{inh|en|ang|bēon}}, which shared its past tense with the verb {{m|ang|wesan}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*wesaną}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*h₂wes-||to reside}}.
* The remaining forms are also from {{inh|en|ang|wesan||to be}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*wesaną}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*h₁ésti}}, from the root {{m|ine-pro|*h₁es-}}.

